methods.copyDataColumns:
For each name in srcColumns, copy all the data at srcColumns.get(name) (with a range of rows defined by
 srcRowSet) to a column indicated by destColumns.get(name) (with a range of rows defined by destRowSet).

:param srcColumns: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,io.deephaven.engine.table.ChunkSource.WithPrev<? extendsio.deephaven.chunk.attributes.Values>>) - The stamp columns that serve as the source data
:param srcRowSet: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - The keys in the srcColumns we are reading from
:param destColumns: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extendsio.deephaven.engine.table.WritableColumnSource<?>>) - The destination columns we are writing to
:param destRowSet: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - The keys in destColumns we want to write to
:param usePrev: boolean
methods.copyStampColumns:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

For each name in stampColumns: - identify a stamp source (namely 'stampColumns.get(name)') - a row in that stamp
 source (namely 'stampKey') - a stamp dest (namely the column identified by 'destColumns.get(name)') - a bunch of
 destination rows (namely all the rows defined in 'destRowSet') Then "spray" that single source value over those
 destination values.

*Overload 1*  
  :param stampColumns: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extendsio.deephaven.engine.table.ColumnSource<?>>) - The stamp columns that serve as the source data
  :param stampKey: (long) - The source key
  :param destColumns: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extendsio.deephaven.engine.table.WritableColumnSource<?>>) - The destination columns we are "spraying" to
  :param destRowSet: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - The keys in destColumns we want to write to
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param stampColumns: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extendsio.deephaven.engine.table.ColumnSource<?>>) - The stamp columns that serve as the source data
  :param stampKey: (long) - The source key
  :param destColumns: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.sources.SingleValueColumnSource<?>>) - The destination columns we are writing to
